    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I want to create a satellite map with intensities from the relief. I use this script:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt begin Marble_Intes png\r\n\tgmt basemap -RBR -JM15c -Baf\r\n#\tgmt basemap -R=AF -JM15c -Baf\r\n\tgmt grdgradient @earth_relief_20m -Nt1 -A45 -Gintens.nc\r\n#\tgmt grdinfo intens.nc\r\n\tgmt grdimage @earth_day_20m -Iintens.nc\r\ngmt end\r\n```\r\nI found two things: \r\n\r\nFirst, when I run `gmt grdgradient` without -RBR I get a grid from all the world besides in the previous line I define -RBR (Brazil). Is this suppose to work this way? Or should `grdgradient` take the region from the previous line? Not sure if it is a bug or should be a feature request.\r\n\r\nThe second issue is related with the region. When I use `\tgmt basemap -RBR -JM15c -Baf` I get:\r\n\r\n\r\n`grdimage [ERROR]: Requested region exceeds illumination extent` and an empty frame: \r\n\r\n\r\n![Marble_Intes_Br](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/142642143-80223dcc-73fc-4b03-b6df-100c89f0977c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nBut when I use -R=AF or R=EU I got this message and the figure is ok. It seems there is an issue with negative longitudes. \r\n\r\n```\r\ngrdsample [WARNING]: Output sampling interval in x exceeds input interval and may lead to aliasing.\r\ngrdsample [WARNING]: Output sampling interval in y exceeds input interval and may lead to aliasing.\r\n\r\n```\r\n![Marble_Intes](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/142641753-1e9e02ec-d9ae-40a0-9f63-1f79864f4e3b.png)\r\n\r\nIf I use `gmt basemap -R-72/-29/-35/20 -JM15c -Baf` I get the same warnings and the figure is ok:\r\n\r\n![Marble_Intes](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/142681771-56aea86d-9e9d-4a63-b1c4-ed96a01399d5.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
